{
  "texts": [
    "Changes in the gut microbiome: from infancy to adulthood and beyond Studies have shown that the gut microbiome of infants undergoes significant changes during the first 3 years of life, with differences observed between populations and influenced by factors, such as delivery mode.",
    "Yatsunenko et al. (2012) compared fecal samples from Amerindians in Venezuela and residents of U.S. metropolitan areas, finding that the gut microbiome exhibited similar functional maturation patterns across the initial 3 years of life across populations.",
    "Palmer et al.",
    "(2007) also, observed substantial variation in the composition of gut bacteria in infants during the first year of life, with reduced variation within twin pairs and decreased variation with age.",
    "Orrhage and Nord (1999) emphasized the impact of delivery mode on the infant microbiome (Fanaro et al., 2003; Penders et al., 2006; Yatsunenko et al., 2012)."
  ]
}